-- LMA Elects Griffiths, Horne and Rainbow as New Directors at AGM
-- B y   S t e p h e n   M o r r i s
-- 2012-06-21T11:56:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-21/lma-elects-griffiths-horne-and-rainbow-as-new-directors-at-agm.html
The  Loan Market Association , the
trade group for syndicated loan underwriters in  Europe , said it
appointed three new directors.  Charles Griffiths of Bank of Tokyo-Mitsubishi UFJ Ltd.,
Babson Capital Europe Ltd.’s Martin Horne, and Graham Rainbow of
Alcentra Ltd. were elected at its annual general meeting
yesterday, according to an e-mailed statement.  Roland Boehm, head of loans at Commerzbank AG, was
reappointed as chairman of the London-based organization, and
Richard Basham at Citigroup Inc., Nick Jansa of Deutsche Bank AG
and Richard Munn of Oak Hill Advisors Europe LLP were
reappointed as vice-chairmen at the following board meeting, the
LMA said.  “Membership of the LMA continues to rise and currently
stands at an all-time high of 486 organisations,” Boehm said in
the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
